Omega Pharma Revenue Growth Stalls, Abandons Full-Year Forecast

-- B y   J o h n   M a r t e n s
-- 
2011-10-13T15:45:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-13/omega-pharma-revenue-growth-stalls-abandons-full-year-forecast.html
Omega Pharma (OME)  NV, the distributor of
pharmacy products that founder Marc Coucke wants to take
private, said revenue growth slowed to 1 percent in the third
quarter and abandoned its full-year revenue forecast.  Revenue in the three months that ended Sept. 30 rose to
202.4 million euros from 200.3 million euros a year earlier, the
Nazareth, Belgium-based company said today in a statement on its
website.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Martens at 
 jmartens1@bloomberg.net  